# 17_toolbar_oneoffs_buttons — substrate-layer suite for the top-level
# toolbar one-off buttons (s197 m1).
#
# Substrate-style test (per TESTING.md grandfather clause). Each
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# the label query reads back. All buttons in this slice are icon-only
# (set_icon_name, no set_label), so the label query returns "" — that
# round-trip is the substrate-contract assertion.
#
# Scope (s197 m1): the four top-level toolbar one-off button sets
# expanded to 18 substrate widgets via helper-signature threading
# (same shape as s196 m1's make_pop_row migration):
#
#   macro button     tb_mb           (1 widget — top-level toolbar)
#
#   stroke popover   pop_tb_strk_cb / cr / cs   (Cap: Butt / Round / Square)
#                    pop_tb_strk_jm / jr / jb   (Join: Miter / Round / Bevel)
#
#   align popover    pop_tb_align_l / ch / r / t / cv / b   (6 align)
#                    pop_tb_align_dh / dv                   (2 distribute)
#
#   bool popover     tb_bop_un / sb / in        (Union / Subtract / Intersect)
#
# All 18 buttons are icon-only. The substrate contract verified here
# is: abbrev → ScriptableRegistry resolution → query_leaf dispatch →
# get_label() returning empty string.
#
# Side effects: none. The Button substrate's `click` verb is not
# exercised — these buttons emit signals (sig_align, sig_bool_op,
# sig_macro_run) that depend on canvas selection state, and firing
# them with no selection would either no-op (align gates on
# align_enabled, bool gates on bool_enabled) or change application
# state in ways the test can't restore. Substrate-addressability +
# verb dispatch are already proven across the corpus; this test
# focuses on the new abbrevs landing in the registry cleanly.
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.

#[sub] Macro button — icon-only, label is empty.

assert tb_mb label == ""

#[sub] Stroke popover cap buttons — three icon-only buttons.

assert pop_tb_strk_cb label == ""
assert pop_tb_strk_cr label == ""
assert pop_tb_strk_cs label == ""

#[sub] Stroke popover join buttons — three icon-only buttons.

assert pop_tb_strk_jm label == ""
assert pop_tb_strk_jr label == ""
assert pop_tb_strk_jb label == ""

#[sub] Align popover align row — six icon-only buttons (L / CH / R / T / CV / B).

assert pop_tb_align_l  label == ""
assert pop_tb_align_ch label == ""
assert pop_tb_align_r  label == ""
assert pop_tb_align_t  label == ""
assert pop_tb_align_cv label == ""
assert pop_tb_align_b  label == ""

#[sub] Align popover distribute row — two icon-only buttons (DH / DV).

assert pop_tb_align_dh label == ""
assert pop_tb_align_dv label == ""

#[sub] Bool popover — three icon-only buttons (Union / Subtract / Intersect).

assert tb_bop_un label == ""
assert tb_bop_sb label == ""
assert tb_bop_in label == ""

#[sub] Done. 18 new substrate widgets, all addressable.
